                  "type":"string",
                  "value":"Christine walked clumsily to the boarding area with her two hand-carry bags. They were bulky, and jingling like Christmas chimes. She rested them on a sofa and heaved. She continued to struggle up a small flight of stairs before finally reaching her boarding gate. She sat next to her luggage and rested. \n\nIn her peripheral sight, a lady gently placed her coat over the backrest of the seat next to her. She turned and caught a glimpse of the name tag clipped neatly on that elegant navy blue: \n\n\"A. Clarke\"\n\nShe looked up and saw a beautiful female pilot. The pilot left not long after fumbling with her pager. Christine closed and rested her eyes as she await the boarding announcement.\n\n"
